      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROBLEN RANGER (3) scored at Hamilton two runs ago before having his colours lowered when sixth at his latest appearance over 2190m at this track, beaten 22 metres. Likely to get all the favours from this nice draw. Won't find this any harder and he can find winning ways. CALEDONIAN TERRA (9) drew wide last start and was easily accounted for, beaten 30 metres into eighth at Terang over 1680m. Hard to know where he gets from this slightly awkward draw. This should be an easier assignment so he is in the right race to return to form. FAMOUS LABEL (8) finished second last start over 2190m here. Generally runs very well at this circuit so can play a big role. PRESIDENTIALCHANGE (2) must be included on the back of some solid recent form, most recently when fifth at this course over 2190m. Favours well from the low draw.",
